%claude:
This chapter covers the memory allocator: from the [[sbrk]]
system call that extends the heap, through the pool-based
allocator that manages free blocks, to the [[malloc]]/[[free]]
interface that programs use. The allocator organizes memory
into arenas obtained from [[sbrk]], with free blocks managed
in a binary tree for efficient best-fit allocation.

