%******************************************************************************
\chapter{Regular Expressions}
%******************************************************************************
\label{chap:regexp}
% libregexp/

%https://swtch.com/~rsc/regexp/

%claude:
[[libregexp]] provides the shared regular expression library
used by programs that don't have their own engine (unlike
[[grep]], which has a built-in DFA matcher for speed). The
library uses an NFA (nondeterministic finite automaton)
approach, which guarantees linear-time matching regardless
of the pattern---unlike backtracking engines (as in Perl or
Python) that can take exponential time on certain inputs.
See Russ Cox's well-known articles on regular expression
matching for a thorough comparison.

