\subsection{Software architecture}

% _xxx = private

% rely on shared memory and futex for synchro.
% ainc, adec. (atomic inc, atomic dec)

% channels are structured in shared memory between processes and
% threads. Used concurrently.

%claude:
The architecture has two levels: OS-level processes (procs)
provide true parallelism via [[rfork(RFMEM)]], while
user-level threads within each proc are cooperatively
scheduled using [[setjmp]]/[[longjmp]]. Channels sit in
shared memory, protected by a single global [[chanlock]],
and use the [[rendezvous]] system call to block/wake
threads across proc boundaries. Functions prefixed with
\verb+_+ are internal; the public API is [[threadcreate]],
[[proccreate]], [[send]], [[recv]], [[alt]], etc.

