\subsection{Concurrency buiding blocks}

%claude:
[[Ref]] is a thread-safe reference counter. [[incref]] and
[[decref]] use atomic operations ([[ainc]]/[[adec]]) so they
work correctly even when called from different procs sharing
memory. [[decref]] returns the new count, so the caller can
free the object when it reaches zero.

<<struct [[Ref]]>>=
struct Ref {
    long	ref;
};
@

<<function [[incref]]>>=
void
incref(Ref *r)
{
    ainc(&r->ref);
}
@

<<function [[decref]]>>=
long
decref(Ref *r)
{
    return adec(&r->ref);
}
@


<<global [[xincport_lock]]>>=
static Lock xincport_lock;
@
